# Any-word wake keyword spotting (vosk_kws engine, 2026-07-05): torch-free,
# Apache-2.0, universal CPU wheels; per-language model fetched at setup, not
# bundled. See pyproject.toml note. CAP below 0.3.45: that release ships NO
# macOS wheel, and the universal lock must stay installable on every OS (AP-23).
vosk>=0.3.44,<0.3.45
# Local VAD (silero-vad → torch), webrtcvad-wheels and the Porcupine wake engine
# (pvporcupine) are NOT base deps: they live in the pyproject.toml [local-voice]
# extra per the cloud-first doctrine (CLAUDE.md §3). torch must never land in the
# base lockfile — it pulls a multi-GB, GPU-specific CUDA wheel stack (nvidia-*),
# which is unresolvable on a plain PyPI install and bricks the installer for every
# non-maintainer machine.

